237
00:10:45.274 --> 00:10:46.400
[Paula] Under His eye.

238
00:10:49.195 --> 00:10:51.197
-[basket thuds. items clattering]
-[gasps]

239
00:10:51.947 --> 00:10:53.783
Clean that up immediately.

240
00:10:53.866 --> 00:10:55.117
Yes. Mrs. MacKenzie.

241
00:10:55.201 --> 00:10:57.244
-[Guardian 1] Everything check out?
-[Guardian 1] Yes. Let's go.

242
00:11:01.666 --> 00:11:03.000
[front door closes]

243
00:11:05.044 --> 00:11:06.962
[tissue paper rustling]

244
00:11:07.046 --> 00:11:10.007
A woman in the Florist Shop
almost got me caught today.

245
00:11:11.175 --> 00:11:12.968
She was terrified.

246
00:11:13.052 --> 00:11:14.595
She said she needs you to move her.

247
00:11:15.805 --> 00:11:17.014
[softly] Shit.

248
00:11:17.556 --> 00:11:18.891
Is something happening?

249
00:11:19.975 --> 00:11:22.228
This morning. I had to walk
past three dead bodies.

250
00:11:22.311 --> 00:11:23.729
Lower your voice.

251
00:11:25.022 --> 00:11:28.275
Gilead's retaliating
for what happened with the bus.

252
00:11:29.151 --> 00:11:31.237
Has Commander Hayes'
daughter said anything?

253
00:11:31.320 --> 00:11:32.697
Her father take any trips?

254
00:11:32.780 --> 00:11:34.657
-Commander...?
-Shunammite.

255
00:11:34.740 --> 00:11:36.992
No. Are you even listening to me?

256
00:11:37.076 --> 00:11:39.453
Those people that they hung were Mayday.

257
00:11:39.537 --> 00:11:41.205
I have to get the fuck out of here.

258
00:11:41.288 --> 00:11:42.915
It's too dangerous.

259
00:11:42.998 --> 00:11:44.333
You knew that coming in.

260
00:11:44.417 --> 00:11:46.961
Yeah. coming in. I assumed you guys
had an organized operation.

261
00:11:47.044 --> 00:11:49.672
[scoffs] What. so you thought
it would just go smoothly?

262
00:11:49.755 --> 00:11:51.465
No bumps? It's a rebellion!

263
00:11:51.549 --> 00:11:53.426
Who do I talk to
about getting out of here?

264
00:11:53.509 --> 00:11:55.928
-[scoffs]
-I don't trust you guys anymore.

265
00:11:56.011 --> 00:11:57.930
And what about the trust we put in you?

266
00:11:58.013 --> 00:12:01.767
We have never had someone get
this close to these girls. their fathers.

267
00:12:01.851 --> 00:12:03.561
the men who run this country.

268
00:12:04.103 --> 00:12:05.229
We waited for this.

269
00:12:05.312 --> 00:12:07.189
[♪ tense music playing]

270
00:12:07.273 --> 00:12:09.233
If you leave now.

271
00:12:09.316 --> 00:12:11.235
we may never have the chance again.

272
00:12:12.528 --> 00:12:14.655
-We need you to do this.
-Do what?

273
00:12:14.739 --> 00:12:17.116
What's the goalpost?

274
00:12:17.199 --> 00:12:18.826
When do I get to leave?

275
00:12:20.119 --> 00:12:21.495
I don't know.

276
00:12:21.579 --> 00:12:23.497
Fuck you.

277
00:12:23.581 --> 00:12:25.291
Find out.

278
00:12:25.374 --> 00:12:28.043
Look. if you get something helpful.

279
00:12:28.127 --> 00:12:30.504
information that really
makes a difference.

280
00:12:30.588 --> 00:12:32.882
at least they'll feel like
they got some return on investment.

281
00:12:32.965 --> 00:12:35.634
Just don't get caught and hung
while I do it?

282
00:12:36.844 --> 00:12:38.304
[front door opens]

283
00:12:38.971 --> 00:12:41.599
[♪ tense music continues]

284
00:12:58.157 --> 00:13:00.284
[indistinct radio chatter]

285
00:13:00.367 --> 00:13:03.078
[dog barking]

286
00:13:03.162 --> 00:13:05.748
[♪ tense music continues]

287
00:13:14.089 --> 00:13:16.258
[Daisy] <i>This wasn't just a tea</i>
<i>in honor of the Aunts.</i>

288
00:13:16.342 --> 00:13:20.679
<i>It was the last chance for the top Greens</i>
<i>to show they're Wife material.</i>

289
00:13:22.014 --> 00:13:25.476
<i>Running a High Commander's house</i>
<i>was definitely not for the fainthearted.</i>

290
00:13:25.559 --> 00:13:27.770
<i>The Aunts needed to see</i>
<i>who could handle the pressure</i>

291
00:13:27.853 --> 00:13:29.730
<i>and who would break.</i>

292
00:13:29.814 --> 00:13:33.442
<i>They would end up with losers.</i>
<i>abusers. or worse.</i>

293
00:13:33.526 --> 00:13:36.362
<i>One stumble and you</i>
<i>could be forever fucked.</i>

294
00:13:37.947 --> 00:13:40.241
<i>Welcome to my world. ladies.</i>

295
00:13:42.243 --> 00:13:44.703
Blessed day. our most cherished guests.

296
00:13:44.787 --> 00:13:48.374
What an honor
to welcome you all here today.

297
00:13:48.457 --> 00:13:52.920
We are so grateful for how well
you've groomed our girls for marriage.

298
00:13:53.003 --> 00:13:55.297
I'm sure it was no small task. [chuckles]

299
00:13:56.632 --> 00:13:58.717
Please. enjoy this afternoon

300
00:13:58.801 --> 00:14:01.220
as a humble token of our appreciation.

301
00:14:01.303 --> 00:14:04.473
We are but vessels for His will.

302
00:14:04.557 --> 00:14:08.519
And the girls are eager to show
their appreciation as well.

303
00:14:09.103 --> 00:14:11.355
Isn't that right. Jehosheba?

304
00:14:11.438 --> 00:14:13.148
Yes. Mother.

305
00:14:13.774 --> 00:14:15.651
God has been so generous

306
00:14:15.734 --> 00:14:18.612
in blessing us all with the best teachers.

307
00:14:19.572 --> 00:14:22.408
And I plan to carry the wisdom
you have taught us

308
00:14:22.491 --> 00:14:24.827
for the rest of my life. [chuckles]

309
00:14:27.538 --> 00:14:28.747
[Aunt Lydia] Hmm.

310
00:14:29.456 --> 00:14:30.499
Shall we begin?

311
00:14:30.583 --> 00:14:32.001
Please. follow me.

312
00:14:37.631 --> 00:14:40.634
[Daisy] <i>Perfect nails. tailored dresses.</i>

313
00:14:40.718 --> 00:14:43.470
<i>Meanwhile. these women</i>
<i>are all married to war criminals.</i>

314
00:14:43.554 --> 00:14:45.723
<i>Mrs. MacKenzie is the alpha here.</i>

315
00:14:45.806 --> 00:14:48.392
<i>because she's married</i>
<i>to the most important Commander.</i>

316
00:14:48.475 --> 00:14:49.935
<i>She has power.</i>

317
00:14:50.019 --> 00:14:51.687
<i>Reflected. but still.</i>

318
00:14:51.770 --> 00:14:53.856
<i>That's what all these girls</i>
<i>desperately want.</i>

319
00:14:53.939 --> 00:14:55.858
<i>Power is survival in Gilead.</i>

320
00:14:55.941 --> 00:14:57.735
Given the most recent troubles.

321
00:14:57.818 --> 00:15:01.947
are you concerned some Commanders
will-- will miss the Ball?

322
00:15:02.031 --> 00:15:04.992
All is as the Lord intends.

323
00:15:05.075 --> 00:15:06.076
Praise be.

324
00:15:06.160 --> 00:15:08.412
[Daisy] <i>Jehosheba's father</i>
<i>designed the Colonies.</i>

325
00:15:08.495 --> 00:15:10.205
<i>He took a trip to visit them recently.</i>

326
00:15:10.289 --> 00:15:11.707
<i>A piece of intel I picked up</i>

327
00:15:11.790 --> 00:15:15.461
<i>when Jehosheba complained her Marthas</i>
<i>slacked off during his absence.</i>

328
00:15:15.544 --> 00:15:16.962
Is it more prudent to postpone

329
00:15:17.046 --> 00:15:21.550
until we're sure that the dust has settled
on all this... ugliness?

330
00:15:21.634 --> 00:15:23.177
All will be well.

331
00:15:23.260 --> 00:15:24.762
[Daisy] <i>Becka's parents are nobodies.</i>

332
00:15:24.845 --> 00:15:27.306
<i>so her mom has to make nice</i>
<i>with everybody.</i>

333
00:15:27.389 --> 00:15:30.267
The Commanders will be there.
You have no reason to worry.

334
00:15:30.351 --> 00:15:32.227
I will trust in the Aunts. as always.

335
00:15:32.311 --> 00:15:33.812
[group chattering]

336
00:15:33.896 --> 00:15:35.147
[Paula] Ladies?

337
00:15:35.230 --> 00:15:38.359
Aunt Lydia. would you do us the honor?

338
00:15:40.194 --> 00:15:44.114
Heavenly Father. we offer
this bounty and abundance in thanks...

339
00:15:44.198 --> 00:15:46.742
[Daisy] <i>Heavenly Father. or Mother.</i>

340
00:15:46.825 --> 00:15:50.079
<i>Goddess of the Earth. if you really exist.</i>

341
00:15:50.162 --> 00:15:52.498
<i>strike lightning through</i>
<i>these bitches' hairdos</i>

342
00:15:52.581 --> 00:15:55.084
<i>and send a helicopter</i>
<i>to get me out of Gilead.</i>

343
00:15:55.167 --> 00:15:56.293
...and these Thy gifts.

344
00:15:56.377 --> 00:15:58.671
which we are about to receive
from Thy bounty.

345
00:15:58.754 --> 00:16:00.756
-through Christ. our Lord...
-[Daisy] <i>Also.</i>

346
00:16:00.839 --> 00:16:02.132
<i>I'd love a Big Mac.</i>

347
00:16:02.216 --> 00:16:03.842
-...Amen.
-[all] Amen.

348
00:16:03.926 --> 00:16:04.969
Amen.

349
00:16:06.178 --> 00:16:09.431
Let's have some tea. [chuckles]

350
00:16:10.432 --> 00:16:12.685
[chatter. laughter]

351
00:16:12.768 --> 00:16:14.603
[tea kettles whistling]

352
00:16:14.687 --> 00:16:16.563
[overlapping chatter continues]

353
00:16:16.647 --> 00:16:17.815
[Daisy] <i>From what I can tell.</i>

354
00:16:17.898 --> 00:16:21.735
<i>these girls aren't expected</i>
<i>to make anything or do anything.</i>

355
00:16:21.819 --> 00:16:25.614
<i>It's all been bought at a shop</i>
<i>or prepared by their Marthas.</i>

356
00:16:25.698 --> 00:16:28.325
<i>Their only job is to make sure</i>
<i>everything is perfect.</i>

357
00:16:29.118 --> 00:16:32.204
<i>That usually involves bossing</i>
<i>around the people below them.</i>

358
00:16:32.287 --> 00:16:34.498
<i>which they're fucking great at.</i>

359
00:16:34.581 --> 00:16:37.376
Hmm. Mm. The color.

360
00:16:37.459 --> 00:16:39.712
It's too light.
You didn't brew it long enough.

361
00:16:39.795 --> 00:16:42.381
It's jasmine tea.
It's supposed to be light.

362
00:16:43.507 --> 00:16:44.925
If you brew it too long. it gets bitter.

363
00:16:45.009 --> 00:16:46.927
-Make it again!
-[cup shatters]

364
00:16:48.178 --> 00:16:50.723
[whining] Why are you doing this to me?

365
00:16:50.806 --> 00:16:52.099
[Jehosheba crying]

366
00:16:52.182 --> 00:16:54.768
I'll make you a new one.
Don't distress yourself.

367
00:16:58.272 --> 00:16:59.815
-Don't worry.
-It's okay.

368
00:16:59.898 --> 00:17:02.192
-Don't worry about it. They'll clean up.
-My Martha brewed extra tea

369
00:17:02.276 --> 00:17:04.069
if you want to use some of ours.

370
00:17:06.447 --> 00:17:08.866
It's lovely. Thank you. Rosa.

371
00:17:08.949 --> 00:17:10.117
You got this.

372
00:17:15.789 --> 00:17:17.624
I feel so bad for them.

373
00:17:18.417 --> 00:17:21.211
For that to happen right
at the start of their season.

374
00:17:21.712 --> 00:17:23.172
You mean. the bus?

375
00:17:24.798 --> 00:17:28.052
I hope that they find every
single one of those terrorists

376
00:17:28.135 --> 00:17:31.055
and gender traitors
and string them up like rats.

377
00:17:31.138 --> 00:17:32.890
[tea kettle whistling]

378
00:17:36.393 --> 00:17:38.270
Can I get you more ginger ale?

379
00:17:39.938 --> 00:17:41.273
Aren't you sweet?

380
00:17:41.356 --> 00:17:43.650
[chuckling] No. thank you. I'm fine.

381
00:17:44.651 --> 00:17:46.612
[Marthas clapping slowly]

382
00:17:46.695 --> 00:17:47.988
Best of luck. girls!

383
00:17:48.072 --> 00:17:51.283
[clapping continues]

384
00:17:51.366 --> 00:17:57.539
[♪ eerie. whimsical music playing]

385
00:17:57.998 --> 00:18:00.292
[slow marching footsteps]

386
00:18:10.511 --> 00:18:12.596
[♪ music fades out]

387
00:18:27.820 --> 00:18:31.406
[♪ spirited orchestral music playing]

388
00:18:39.289 --> 00:18:40.916
Excellent form. girls.

389
00:18:43.377 --> 00:18:47.840
♪♪

390
00:19:13.073 --> 00:19:15.117
Wonderful. isn't it?

391
00:19:20.372 --> 00:19:21.999
Mm.

392
00:19:22.124 --> 00:19:24.084
[Miriam's mother] [whispers]
Well done. Miriam.

393
00:19:28.964 --> 00:19:31.216
[♪ music darkens]

394
00:19:52.738 --> 00:19:55.449
[♪ spirited music continues]

395
00:19:56.325 --> 00:19:57.784
[softly clapping]

396
00:20:08.587 --> 00:20:10.130
-[china clattering]
-Miriam!

397
00:20:10.214 --> 00:20:11.673
[Miriam gasps]

398
00:20:11.757 --> 00:20:12.758
[♪ music stops]

399
00:20:14.218 --> 00:20:16.553
-[Miriam breathing shakily]
-[Aunt] Oh dear.

400
00:20:16.637 --> 00:20:19.097
I'm so. so sorry. Mrs. Ma--

401
00:20:19.181 --> 00:20:20.849
MacKenzie. I'll go get my Martha now.

402
00:20:20.933 --> 00:20:23.185
It's no worry at all. dear.

403
00:21:00.138 --> 00:21:02.391
[breathing shakily]

404
00:21:05.519 --> 00:21:08.855
[exhales sharply]
I-- I can't believe I did that.

405
00:21:08.939 --> 00:21:12.651
It was a mistake. but
"The Lord waits to be gracious to us."

406
00:21:12.734 --> 00:21:15.404
so... fingers crossed.

407
00:21:18.615 --> 00:21:20.242
What happened?

408
00:21:20.909 --> 00:21:22.369
She spilled her tea.

409
00:21:25.289 --> 00:21:26.873
That's it?

410
00:21:34.756 --> 00:21:38.844
[voice shaking] Aunt Estee.
Pray. I'm so sorry to have failed you.

411
00:21:38.927 --> 00:21:41.096
All one can do is her best.

412
00:21:42.306 --> 00:21:45.058
Pray. I won't be married off
to a man from the Colonies.

413
00:21:45.142 --> 00:21:46.435
will I?

414
00:21:47.894 --> 00:21:50.439
Whatever happens is in God's plan for you.

415
00:21:50.522 --> 00:21:52.107
[girl] [whispers]
How could she do that?

416
00:21:54.151 --> 00:21:56.403
[softly] By His hand.

417
00:21:59.114 --> 00:22:00.198
-It's okay.
-It's okay.

418
00:22:00.282 --> 00:22:01.742
-[Miriam sniffling]
-It's okay.

419
00:22:01.825 --> 00:22:04.119
[Miriam sobbing]

420
00:22:04.202 --> 00:22:07.164
[♪ somber music playing]

421
00:22:07.247 --> 00:22:12.169
-Breathe. breathe. It's okay.
-[continues sobbing]

422
00:22:13.045 --> 00:22:15.630
[Daisy] <i>I didn't understand it then.</i>

423
00:22:17.132 --> 00:22:19.259
<i>I'm not sure I understand it now.</i>

424
00:22:20.510 --> 00:22:22.137
<i>But it was real to them.</i>

425
00:22:24.056 --> 00:22:26.224
[Daisy]<i> As real as anything</i>
<i>I've ever felt.</i>

426
00:22:27.684 --> 00:22:30.312
<i>As real as a heart attack.</i>

427
00:22:30.395 --> 00:22:31.813
<i>Or a hanging.</i>

428
00:22:49.247 --> 00:22:50.916
[fire crackling]

429
00:22:50.999 --> 00:22:52.876
[birds chirping]

430
00:22:59.758 --> 00:23:01.468
Blessed day. Are you lost?

431
00:23:04.763 --> 00:23:06.640
Blessed day. sir.

432
00:23:08.642 --> 00:23:10.394
Well. what brings you in here?

433
00:23:11.436 --> 00:23:13.772
[♪ tense music playing]

434
00:23:13.855 --> 00:23:17.484
Forgive me. The chocolate on your desk.

435
00:23:17.567 --> 00:23:18.902
sir.

436
00:23:21.780 --> 00:23:25.409
I haven't had any since
before I came to Gilead.

437
00:23:25.492 --> 00:23:29.121
[♪ tense music continues]

438
00:23:39.756 --> 00:23:41.091
I'm sorry.

439
00:23:42.175 --> 00:23:45.512
I'll accept whatever correction
you deem appropriate. sir.

440
00:23:45.595 --> 00:23:48.598
♪♪

441
00:23:57.190 --> 00:23:59.818
I used to bring these home
to my daughter when she was little.

442
00:24:03.530 --> 00:24:05.740
But I don't think she likes them anymore.

443
00:24:10.579 --> 00:24:14.291
Aunt Lydia. she paired me with Miss Agnes.

444
00:24:20.464 --> 00:24:24.384
I have much to learn
and she sets such a pious example.

445
00:24:24.468 --> 00:24:26.803
-[♪ tense music fades]
-[birds chirping]

446
00:24:28.096 --> 00:24:30.390
And she's been so kind to me.

447
00:24:32.434 --> 00:24:34.352
Yes. she's a very good girl.

448
00:24:38.148 --> 00:24:39.858
I suppose she's not a girl now.

449
00:24:45.614 --> 00:24:47.407
Is she happy?

450
00:24:53.038 --> 00:24:56.041
"Joyful indeed are those
whose God is the Lord."

451
00:24:59.211 --> 00:25:00.378
[sighs]

452
00:25:03.048 --> 00:25:05.217
You must be needed at the party.

453
00:25:05.300 --> 00:25:07.052
Go in grace.

454
00:25:07.886 --> 00:25:11.389
[♪ solemn music playing]

455
00:25:17.145 --> 00:25:18.271
[door shuts]

456
00:25:18.355 --> 00:25:20.607
[exhales heavily]

457
00:25:40.460 --> 00:25:42.754
So. how do you think you did?

458
00:25:43.630 --> 00:25:46.216
-Fine?
-Fine.

459
00:25:46.299 --> 00:25:48.468
[indistinct chatter]

460
00:25:50.178 --> 00:25:52.222
[whispering] Well. I'm sure you guys
looked better than Miriam.

461
00:25:52.305 --> 00:25:53.848
[whispering] That wasn't her fault.

462
00:25:53.932 --> 00:25:56.184
Who cares? She chunked it.

463
00:25:56.268 --> 00:25:57.727
Poor Miriam.

464
00:25:57.811 --> 00:25:59.896
Girls. back into the parlor. Off you go.

465
00:26:04.317 --> 00:26:05.944
[softly] I'm so proud of you.

466
00:26:06.027 --> 00:26:07.445
Thank you. Rosa.

467
00:26:09.072 --> 00:26:10.490
[indistinct chatter]

468
00:26:12.742 --> 00:26:16.413
[♪ light music playing]

469
00:26:18.748 --> 00:26:20.417
[whispering] I know what you're doing.

470
00:26:20.500 --> 00:26:23.003
Uh. I wasn't doing anything.

471
00:26:24.838 --> 00:26:26.673
Staring at a man like that?

472
00:26:26.756 --> 00:26:30.051
Maybe you don't care what happens to you.

473
00:26:30.135 --> 00:26:32.470
but you can get him in a lot of trouble.

474
00:26:32.554 --> 00:26:34.764
Guardians are punished for a lot less.

475
00:26:34.848 --> 00:26:37.642
[Rosa] Come now. it's time
for the Commander's Cake.

476
00:26:38.852 --> 00:26:41.813
Just so you know.
I used to have a lot of guy friends.

477
00:26:42.606 --> 00:26:45.984
It was totally platonic.
and it wasn't a big deal.

478
00:27:18.058 --> 00:27:20.810
Ladies. the Lord revels

479
00:27:20.894 --> 00:27:23.480
in how you have
all comported yourselves today.

480
00:27:24.147 --> 00:27:26.441
You have done your mothers proud.

481
00:27:26.524 --> 00:27:28.276
And you have done us proud.

482
00:27:28.902 --> 00:27:31.488
And so. we finish with a Gilead tradition.

483
00:27:31.571 --> 00:27:33.531
The Commander's Cake.

484
00:27:33.615 --> 00:27:37.327
Inside one of these slices.
a hidden treasure.

485
00:27:37.410 --> 00:27:39.871
Shall we find out who is so lucky?

486
00:27:39.954 --> 00:27:43.667
Who will have His light shined upon her
at this juncture?

487
00:27:43.750 --> 00:27:47.379
Oh. let them eat their cake. Vidala!

488
00:27:47.462 --> 00:27:48.922
Dig in. girls.

489
00:27:52.384 --> 00:27:54.302
[softly chuckles] Hmm.

490
00:27:54.386 --> 00:27:56.429
[dishes clinking]

491
00:27:56.513 --> 00:27:59.099
[group chattering quietly]

492
00:28:00.141 --> 00:28:01.601
[bite crunches]

493
00:28:02.644 --> 00:28:06.690
[♪ curious music playing]

494
00:28:10.026 --> 00:28:11.444
Agnes found the bride!

495
00:28:12.946 --> 00:28:16.157
[Daisy] <i>History has it that whoever gets</i>
<i>the bride is the first to marry.</i>

496
00:28:16.241 --> 00:28:19.244
-[polite applause]
<i>-It's kind of like catching the bouquet.</i>

497
00:28:19.327 --> 00:28:21.162
<i>It's a porcelain bride.</i>

498
00:28:21.246 --> 00:28:24.082
-[mouth squelching]
<i>-Not a plastic one.</i>

499
00:28:24.165 --> 00:28:25.834
<i>There's no plastic in Gilead.</i>

500
00:28:25.917 --> 00:28:26.918
[tooth pops]

501
00:28:30.004 --> 00:28:31.172
[porcelain clinks]

502
00:28:32.298 --> 00:28:33.466
[Paula gasps]

503
00:28:35.343 --> 00:28:37.470
[gasping and murmuring]

504
00:28:41.599 --> 00:28:42.767
Is it... bad?

505
00:28:42.851 --> 00:28:44.936
Of course. it's bad.

506
00:28:45.019 --> 00:28:47.313
How awful.

507
00:28:47.397 --> 00:28:48.940
And with the Ball so soon.

508
00:28:50.066 --> 00:28:51.901
Don't worry. Paula.

509
00:28:51.985 --> 00:28:55.822
I'll call my husband and make sure
she gets seen right away.

510
00:28:57.449 --> 00:28:58.867
Praise be your kindness.

511
00:28:59.826 --> 00:29:02.787
Go clean up. Agnes. I'll send for a car.

512
00:29:03.496 --> 00:29:05.915
[♪ tense music playing]

513
00:29:06.833 --> 00:29:08.918
Hey. don't worry.

514
00:29:09.002 --> 00:29:10.920
My dad will take good care of you.

515
00:29:11.004 --> 00:29:12.255
I promise.

516
00:29:13.465 --> 00:29:15.842
[♪ tense music continues]

517
00:29:23.683 --> 00:29:26.102
[♪ peppy waiting room Muzak playing]

518
00:29:31.483 --> 00:29:33.568
Have a Blessed day. Commander.

519
00:29:39.824 --> 00:29:43.119
Agnes. Lovely to see you. as always.

520
00:29:43.703 --> 00:29:44.871
Come.

521
00:29:47.957 --> 00:29:49.375
[Daisy] <i>I guess even in Gilead.</i>

522
00:29:49.459 --> 00:29:51.795
<i>no one likes to go to the fucking dentist.</i>

523
00:29:52.712 --> 00:29:54.798
[♪ peppy Muzak continues playing]

524
00:30:11.856 --> 00:30:14.067
You're in luck.

525
00:30:14.150 --> 00:30:16.778
A simple bonding will do the trick.
Very routine.

526
00:30:19.322 --> 00:30:20.490
Praise be.

527
00:30:20.573 --> 00:30:23.076
This is just a mild sedative.

528
00:30:26.162 --> 00:30:27.413
There we go.

529
00:30:27.497 --> 00:30:30.208
Just recite the Lord's Prayer
and before you know it...

530
00:30:30.291 --> 00:30:33.169
-[clicks button]
-...you'll wake up with a perfect smile.

531
00:30:33.253 --> 00:30:34.796
[gas hissing]

532
00:30:34.879 --> 00:30:37.090
[♪ tense music continues]

533
00:30:38.299 --> 00:30:41.094
[slowly] Our Father. who art in heaven.

534
00:30:41.678 --> 00:30:43.721
Hallowed be Thy name.

535
00:30:43.805 --> 00:30:45.807
Thy kingdom come...

536
00:30:46.558 --> 00:30:49.394
[groggily] Thy will be done...

537
00:30:49.477 --> 00:30:50.687
on Earth...

538
00:30:50.770 --> 00:30:52.063
as it is...

539
00:30:53.773 --> 00:30:55.400
[weakly muttering]

540
00:31:08.121 --> 00:31:10.623
[♪ tense music intensifies]

541
00:31:14.502 --> 00:31:16.796
[♪ peppy Muzak playing]

542
00:31:33.646 --> 00:31:34.981
[whispering] Hey.

543
00:31:35.064 --> 00:31:36.482
Hey.

544
00:31:40.778 --> 00:31:43.489
A chocolate from
Commander MacKenzie's office.

545
00:31:44.449 --> 00:31:46.326
You wanted to know
whose dads were traveling.

546
00:31:46.409 --> 00:31:48.536
The Swiss are neutral.

547
00:31:49.871 --> 00:31:50.914
It's an import.

548
00:31:50.997 --> 00:31:52.457
Look at the back.

549
00:31:56.836 --> 00:31:58.379
Japan has sanctions against Gilead.

550
00:32:01.466 --> 00:32:02.508
What was he doing there?

551
00:32:02.592 --> 00:32:04.552
Why the fuck would I know?

552
00:32:04.636 --> 00:32:05.678
That's your job.

553
00:32:09.849 --> 00:32:13.019
Also. you might want
to be careful with Agnes.

554
00:32:16.940 --> 00:32:18.858
She's in love with you.

555
00:32:20.818 --> 00:32:22.153
Nice work letting that happen.

556
00:32:23.571 --> 00:32:25.073
[door opening]

557
00:32:45.927 --> 00:32:48.012
[♪ tense music playing]

558
00:32:48.972 --> 00:32:50.974
[water running]

559
00:33:07.323 --> 00:33:09.158
[faucet shuts off]

560
00:33:09.242 --> 00:33:10.868
[Dr. Grove] Welcome back.

561
00:33:13.871 --> 00:33:16.666
If you have any pain. tell your mother.

562
00:33:16.749 --> 00:33:18.418
She'll call me.

563
00:33:18.501 --> 00:33:20.878
Oh. and good luck at the Ball.

564
00:33:20.962 --> 00:33:22.714
I'm sure you and Becka will do great.

565
00:33:36.728 --> 00:33:38.438
[fountain trickling]

566
00:33:43.026 --> 00:33:45.028
[vehicle approaching]

567
00:34:08.843 --> 00:34:12.263
[Paula] Okay. come. Let me see.

568
00:34:12.346 --> 00:34:14.682
Smile. Open.

569
00:34:19.103 --> 00:34:22.190
Oh. thank the Lord.
Dr. Grove does beautiful work.

570
00:34:22.982 --> 00:34:24.609
[sighs deeply]

571
00:34:24.692 --> 00:34:26.736
I blame your mother for this.

572
00:34:26.819 --> 00:34:28.696
She gave you weak teeth. didn't she?

573
00:34:30.198 --> 00:34:31.365
Tabitha?

574
00:34:31.449 --> 00:34:33.367
No. not Tabitha.

575
00:34:34.452 --> 00:34:37.830
[sighs] It's not your fault
that you come from weak genes.

576
00:34:39.207 --> 00:34:42.960
That's where that
rebellious streak comes from.

577
00:34:52.887 --> 00:34:54.806
She has a weak chin.

578
00:34:54.889 --> 00:34:56.557
Can't fix that.

579
00:34:58.851 --> 00:35:00.478
[Agnes softly chuckles]

580
00:35:04.774 --> 00:35:09.070
So... how many mothers have you had?

581
00:35:09.737 --> 00:35:10.947
One.

582
00:35:12.031 --> 00:35:14.408
Paula's my stepmother. My mother died.

583
00:35:15.660 --> 00:35:18.162
But your stepmother
mentioned someone else.

584
00:35:19.080 --> 00:35:20.998
Your birth mother?

585
00:35:21.082 --> 00:35:22.667
We don't--

586
00:35:24.335 --> 00:35:27.505
It's rude to talk about that here.

587
00:35:27.588 --> 00:35:29.090
I'm sorry.

588
00:35:32.552 --> 00:35:34.262
My mom died. too.

589
00:35:39.642 --> 00:35:41.144
I'm sorry.

590
00:35:42.395 --> 00:35:44.021
So did my birth mother.

591
00:35:45.356 --> 00:35:47.275
[front door opens. closes]

592
00:35:47.942 --> 00:35:50.820
[Rosa] Daisy. dear.
It's time for you to head back.

593
00:35:50.903 --> 00:35:52.196
Your ride's around the house.

594
00:35:52.280 --> 00:35:53.948
-[package paper rustling]
-The leftover cake.

595
00:35:54.031 --> 00:35:55.575
For you and the other Pearl Girls.

596
00:35:55.658 --> 00:35:56.993
Thank you.

597
00:36:01.914 --> 00:36:04.125
Have a blessed evening. Miss Agnes.

598
00:36:27.356 --> 00:36:30.860
[♪ tense music playing]

599
00:36:39.619 --> 00:36:43.456
[Daisy] <i>A lot later. I found out</i>
<i>what happened to the florist.</i>

600
00:36:43.539 --> 00:36:46.459
<i>She tried to run when</i>
<i>the Eyes came to the shop.</i>

601
00:36:46.542 --> 00:36:48.586
<i>She was shot dead in the street.</i>

602
00:36:52.340 --> 00:36:54.175
<i>I found out her name was Candace.</i>

603
00:36:54.258 --> 00:36:56.636
[♪ tense music continues]

604
00:36:56.719 --> 00:36:58.512
<i>Rest in peace. Candace.</i>

605
00:36:58.596 --> 00:37:00.640
<i>I'm sorry I couldn't help you.</i>

606
00:37:14.946 --> 00:37:17.531
<i>Candace panicked. and now she's dead.</i>

607
00:37:18.741 --> 00:37:20.534
<i>Don't show anything.</i>

608
00:37:20.618 --> 00:37:23.829
<i>No matter what. no matter how much</i>
<i>I'm freaking out inside.</i>

609
00:37:27.708 --> 00:37:30.503
<i>I need to keep my shit together.</i>
<i>like they do.</i>

610
00:37:30.586 --> 00:37:33.005
<i>Like Agnes. like all of them.</i>

611
00:37:33.089 --> 00:37:35.341
<i>I'm sure they're panicking</i>
<i>a lot of the time.</i>

612
00:37:35.424 --> 00:37:37.760
<i>and I don't even see it.</i>

613
00:37:37.843 --> 00:37:40.638
<i>Push it down. You can do it.</i>

614
00:37:40.721 --> 00:37:43.099
<i>That's what they're always</i>
<i>telling us in Gilead.</i>

615
00:37:43.724 --> 00:37:46.269
<i>"God never gives us</i>
<i>more than we can handle."</i>

616
00:37:52.149 --> 00:37:55.444
<i>But that. as they used to say in my world.</i>

617
00:37:55.528 --> 00:37:56.946
<i>is bullshit.</i>

618
00:38:09.917 --> 00:38:11.502
[stall door squeaking]

619
00:38:14.171 --> 00:38:15.298
[lock latches]

620
00:38:19.427 --> 00:38:21.178
[radio static]

621
00:38:21.262 --> 00:38:23.180
[announcer] [on radio]
<i>You're listening to Radio Free Boston</i>

622
00:38:23.264 --> 00:38:24.307
<i>with an urgent warning for--</i>

623
00:38:24.390 --> 00:38:26.100
[radio stops]

624
00:38:27.852 --> 00:38:31.105
[high-pitched tone]

625
00:38:42.325 --> 00:38:43.951
[tone stops]

626
00:38:46.037 --> 00:38:48.205
[stall door creaking]

627
00:38:48.289 --> 00:38:50.791
[♪ soft. suspenseful music playing]

628
00:38:53.461 --> 00:38:55.963
[water running]

629
00:39:11.062 --> 00:39:13.689
♪♪

630
00:39:17.526 --> 00:39:19.528
[♪ music intensifies]

631
00:39:29.914 --> 00:39:31.999
[breathing heavily]

632
00:39:33.250 --> 00:39:34.710
[muffled sobbing]

633
00:39:34.794 --> 00:39:37.963
[muffled wailing]

634
00:39:45.679 --> 00:39:48.974
[gasping]

635
00:39:49.850 --> 00:39:52.937
[gasping sobs]

636
00:41:22.985 --> 00:41:24.904
{\an8}[insects chirring]

637
00:41:26.906 --> 00:41:27.990
[rooster crowing]

638
00:41:28.305 --> 00:42:28.230
